              <tr><td colspan="3"><b>Description</b><br>
This zone is part of the newly discovered continent of Kunark. Please post any and all information you can about the new zone, including the type of zone (town, dungeon, forest, etc), what are the adjacent zones (location would be nice but not necessary), and it's level range. Also feel free to post any new items, NPC's, or landmarks you come across.<br><br>
<b>Player Comments</b> (total:36, showing:1-5) <a href="JavaScript:popComment('comment.php3?type=zone&tid=107')">add</a><br>
<a href="mailto:fagpatrol@hotmail.com">Oscuro</a> of the The Rathe server on Nov. 16, 2000 at 06:47pm said...<br>
Where does the bodyguard spawn at? Any info would help a lot...thanks.<br><br>
<a href="mailto:barblast@wt.net">Fendiwen</a> of the Veeshan server on Nov. 15, 2000 at 01:37pm said...<br>
Alright I just want to clarify a few things.  All the spawns around and in the building where Soothsayer Drelzak spawns have a random chance of being soothsayers or goblin fanatics.  The spawns in the caves and next to the tents surrounding Chief Rukgus have a random chance of being bodyguards.    NOTHING in droga can see invis, having to fight your way all the way down here would be a total waste of time so make sure you have someone who can cast invis with you, and yes every single goblin will agro you even if you're 30 levels above it but if the goblins are green to you you can single pull.   The goblin's agro range is very small so if invis starts wearing off don't panic.  I've gone through droga probably 30 times and have never had an invis wear off at a point where I couldn't step aside and safely recast it.  Hope this helps!<br><br>
<a href="mailto:shrdlu@hotmail.com">Meowse</a> of the Solusek Ro server on Nov. 07, 2000 at 01:31pm said...<br>
TWO-PART POST: PART 2

Once you get to the room where Chief Rok'Gus spawns, just set up camp where he is (up the ramp at the far back of the dungeon).  From there, once you have that spawn split, you can pull things up the ramp for XP, and the respawns aren't fatally bad.  We held down that room (and the surrounding rooms) for about three hours last night, and got Rok'Gus four times.  He dropped his little pig-sticker twice, and the Essence of Dol twice.  No Idol of the Thorned yet...but we're still hoping.  :-)

Oh, and we accidentally got a Shroud of Nature on the way in from the Mines of Nurga zone.

On th whole, this zone is about as undercamped as Kaesora, and has about the same caliber of loot.  The only real difference is that the best mid-level look in Kaesora (the Book of Spirits, int +6 wis +6) is absolutely trivial to get to, and easy to hold down, while Droga is a hard fight all the way to the back, and constant effort to hold down the Chief spawn once you get there.

But then again, I'd much rather have an Idol of the Thorned than a Book of Spirits.  :-)

Bring five friends, pull one room at a time, and be careful.  Good luck!
<br><br>
<a href="mailto:shrdlu@hotmail.com">Meowse</a> of the Solusek Ro server on Nov. 07, 2000 at 01:31pm said...<br>
TWO-PART POST: PART 1

The maps at http://www.eqatlas.com/kunark/templeofdroga.html are quite good. They're not perfect, but they'll get you where you want to go.

We've been doing Droga for the past several nights with a level 51 Druid, a level 43 (now 44; leveled in zone) Warrior, and a level 41 (now 43; leveled in zone) Cleric.  The experience is excellent (we've been averaging about a bubble an hour each for the Warrior and the Cleric; the Druid is along for the ride, except when the rare named is blue), the loot is fine as long as you're fighting the named mobs, and the risk is...moderate.

Specifically, we haven't died yet, but we have gotten pulls of five or six goblins, several of them casters or healers, at the same time.

I wouldn't try this dungeon with a pick-up group of fewer than six people, all between 40 and 50.

However, if your monk is craving an Essence of Dol, or your druid needs a Shroud of Nature, or ANYONE wants an Idol of the Thorned, it's a fine place to go hunting.

Strategies: clear your way to your destination one room at a time.  Don't expect to be able to get singletons; bring a group that can handle three tanks and a cleric, or three tanks and a caster.  If you're careful, though, that should be all you need to bring.<br><br>
